Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setUsefulSkewMode(25.10)                              setUsefulSkewMode(25.10)

Name
       setUsefulSkewMode - Sets global parameters for the skewClock command

Syntax
       setUsefulSkewMode

       [-help]

       [-opt_skew_apply_delay_limits_to_full_flow {true|false}]

       [-opt_skew_delay_pre_cts {true|false}]

       [-opt_skew_macro_only {true | false}]

       [-opt_skew_max_allowed_delay <delay>]

       [-opt_skew_min_allowed_delay <delay>]

       [-opt_skew_no_boundary {true | false}]

       [-reset]

       Sets global parameters for the skewClock command.

       Use  the  getUsefulSkewMode  to return the current settings for the se-
       tUsefulSkewMode command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each setUsefulSkewMode parameter. For a detailed
              description of the command and all of its  parameters,  use  the
              man command:

              man setUsefulSkewMode

       -opt_skew_apply_delay_limits_to_full_flow {true | false}
              When  set to true, specifies that the useful skew limit is to be
              applied to the whole flow. With this setting,  the  Early  Clock
              Flow  is  modified  so  that  pre-existing tool-generated useful
              skews count towards the limit imposed by  the  -opt_skew_max_al-
              lowed_delay  parameter. The tool-generated useful skew comprises
              any  pin  insertion  delay  (PID)  of  category  useful_skew  or
              global_skew. PIDs of other categories are not considered.

              By default, this parameter is set to false, which means the pre-
              existing  skews  are  not considered while calculating the limit
              imposed by using the -opt_skew_max_allowed_delay parameter.

              Default: false

       -opt_skew_delay_pre_cts {true |false}
              Specifies that the useful skew feature is allowed to  delay  se-
              quential elements in preCTS stage, in addition to just advancing
              them.  This  enables a more aggressive algorithm which is recom-
              mended when timing closure is gated by optimal skewing.

              Default:true

       -opt_skew_macro_only {true | false}
              Allows you to limit skewing only for macro cells. When  enabled,
              regular  sequential  elements  (such  as flip-flops) will not be
              skewed.

              Default: false

       -opt_skew_max_allowed_delay <delay>
              Limits the amount of slack (in nanoseconds)  that  the  software
              can  borrow  from  neighboring flip-flops when performing useful
              skew operations. The Innovus delay calculation and RC extraction
              methods might differ from those  of  sign-off  tools,  so  other
              setup  violations  might  occur if the software borrows too much
              slack. By having control over slack borrowing, you  can  prevent
              these  setup  violations. Limiting borrowed skew also limits the
              clock tree skew to avoid large hold violations.

              Value Range: min=0 max=1000

              Default: 1ns

              Note:

              * This parameter is not honored in the  postCTS  mode  of  skew-
                Clock.

              * In  the  non-early clock flow, when skewClock is triggered in-
                side optDesign, and this  parameter  is  set  to  its  default
                value,  the default value of this parameter will change from 1
                to become a certain percentage of clock cycle. This is  deter-
                mined by the software on the basis of internal calculations.

       -opt_skew_min_allowed_delay <delay>
              Allows  the  tool to skip any skewing that would be smaller than
              the minimum delay that is set. The purpose is to avoid  creating
              very  small delay macro models which would not be correctly hon-
              ored during CTS stage but also to reduce  the  amount  of  macro
              models generated.

              Value Range: min=0 max=1000

              Default: 0

              Note:

              * This is supported in both standalone skewClock command and for
                -usefulSkew called within optDesign.

              * Enable  the  -usefulSkew parameter in optDesign by setting se-
                tOptMode -opt_skew true

       -opt_skew_no_boundary {true |false}
              Excludes or includes boundary sequential cells  in  addition  to
              ordinary sequential elements in useful skew calculations.

              Note:  This  parameter  is  applicable  to  preCTS, postCTS, and
              postRoute useful skew behaviors.

              Default: false

       -reset Resets parameters to their default values. The -reset  parameter
              must  be the first parameter specified. If you specify only -re-
              set, the software resets  all  setUsefulSkewMode  parameters  to
              their  default  values.  If you specify parameters after -reset,
              the software resets only those parameters to their default  val-
              ues.

              Any  values  that do not already match the default value and are
              reset will be reported.

Examples
              * The following command resets the -delayPreCts parameter to its
                default value:

                setUsefulSkewMode -reset -opt_skew_delay_pre_cts

              * The following command resets all setUsefulSkewMode  parameters
                to their default values:

                setUsefulSkewMode -reset

              * The  following  command  forces the tool to skew at minimum by
                30ps any elements that can be skewed to improve the setup tim-
                ing slack:

                setUsefulSkewMode -opt_skew_min_allowed_delay 0.03

                skewClock /optDesign -preCts

              * The following command allows the user to  limit  skewing  only
                for macro cells:

                setUsefulSkewMode -opt_skew_macro_only true

                skewClock or optDesign -preCts/-postCts

Related Information
              * getUsefulSkewMode

              * setOptMode

              * skewClock

              * The following topic in the Innovus User Guide

                * Optimizing Timing using Useful Skew

